{"lemma":"عُبابُ","slug":"عُبابُ","root":"ع.ب.ب","root_slug":"ع-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27758","n27759","n27763"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27758","headword_ar":"عَبَابِ","root":"Eb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[a quasi-inf. n., of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaAri","text_ar":"فَجَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAdi","text_ar":"حَمَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", indecl.]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA EabaAbi","text_ar":"لَا عَبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as used in the prov. here following] means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taEub~u fiY AlmaA='i","text_ar":"لَا تَعُبُّ فِى المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S. [Thus in one of my copies of the S: in the other copy the explanation is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taEub~u fY","text_ar":"لَا تَعُبُّ فى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmA'","text_ar":"الماء"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaAbi","text_ar":"عَبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"were an imperative verbal noun: and so in the O, in which the phrase is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA EabaAba","text_ar":"لَا عَبَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEub~a","text_ar":"بَعُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"I think a mistranscription.]) The saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA A^aSaAbati AlZ~ibaA='u AlmaA='a falaA","text_ar":"اـِذَا اَصَابَتِ الظِّبَا=ءُ المَا=ءَ فَلَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaAbi waA_ino lamo tuSibohu falaA A^abaAbi","text_ar":"عَبَابِ وَاـِنْ لَمْ تُصِبْهُ فَلَا اَبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the gazelles find water, they do not drink in the manner termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~N","text_ar":"عَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and when they do not find it, they do not prepare to seek it and to drink it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA; and thus ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaAbi","text_ar":"عَبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAbi","text_ar":"اَبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":") accord. to the Mz, 40th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":": but in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabAba","text_ar":"عَبابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AabAba","text_ar":"اَبابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it is a prov., frequently used by the Arabs in an abridged manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA EbAb wlA AbAb","text_ar":"لا عباب ولا اباب"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the works of Meyd and others; (TA;) and is applied to a man who turns from a thing, not needing it. (Meyd.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27759","headword_ar":"عُبَابٌ","root":"Eb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main body"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a torrent, or flow of water: and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"height and abundance"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (O, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waves, billows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surges,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) thereof (O) or of a thing: (K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first and main portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of water: and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence of running"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~a EubaAbuhu","text_ar":"عَبَّ عُبَابُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, near the end. ―         -b3-  It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aA HaY~N mino ma*oHijK","text_ar":"اـِنَّا حَىٌّ مِنْ مَذْحِجٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EubaAbu $arafihaA walubaAbu salafihaA","text_ar":"عُبَابُ شَرَفِهَا وَلُبَابُ سَلَفِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily we are a tribe"},{"kind":"text","text":"sprung"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from Medh-hij, the chief of their nobility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobles, and the purest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best,"},{"kind":"text","text":"issue]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of their ancestry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the purest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best,"},{"kind":"text","text":"inheritors]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of their ancestral might and glory."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA: only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salafihaA","text_ar":"سَلَفِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this saying being there explained.) And in a trad. of 'Alee, relating to Aboo-Bekr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tirota","text_ar":"طِرْتَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEubaAbihaA wfuzota biHabaAbihaA","text_ar":"بِعُبَابِهَا وفُزْتَ بِحَبَابِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAbN","text_ar":"حَبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA biEubaAbihimo","text_ar":"جَاوُوا بِعُبَابِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with their whole company,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwSap","text_ar":"خُوصَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaf of a palm-tree &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n27763","headword_ar":"عَبَّابٌ","root":"Eb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[app. One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that drinks in the manner termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~N","text_ar":"عَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw AlEab~aAbi","text_ar":"بَنُو العَبَّابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of a people of the Arabs who were thus called because they intermixed with the Persians so that their horses drank ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~ato","text_ar":"عَبَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K, TA, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aribato","text_ar":"شَرِبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA) of the water of the Euphrates. (K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}